{
  "bugs": [
    {
      "description": "In the `getSegments` method, the `end` variable is not checked for infinite coordinates. If the sub-line is unbounded in the positive infinity direction, the `end` point of the last segment will have infinite coordinates, which may cause issues when creating the `Segment` objects.",
      "code": "final Vector3D end   = line.toSpace(new Vector1D(interval.getSup()));"
    },
    {
      "description": "In the `intersection` method, the `includeEndPoints` parameter is not used correctly. The method should return the intersection point if it lies within the range of both sub-lines, regardless of whether the endpoints are included or not. However, the current implementation only considers the intersection point if it is inside both sub-lines, even when `includeEndPoints` is set to `true`.",
      "code": "return ((loc1 != Location.OUTSIDE) && (loc2 != Location.OUTSIDE)) ? v1D : null;"
    }
  ]
}
